# Shell scripts must use LF endings on every platform. A CRLF shebang (`#!/bin/sh\r`)
# makes the Linux loader look for an interpreter literally named "/bin/sh\r", so the
# script fails with `exec: no such file or directory` — this silently breaks the Docker
# entrypoint (and any container/CI shell) when the image is built from a Windows checkout
# with core.autocrlf=true. Pin LF regardless of the contributor's autocrlf setting.
*.sh text eol=lf
